Hi Alan,

the attached patch updates the the personality mechanism,
kernel/exec_domain.c and include/linux/personality.h in particular
to the version from linux-abi.

Follwoing changes are included:

  o autoloading of personality modules through kmod
  o new personalities (e.g. OSR, UW7, solaris) from linux-abi
  o sysctl support for controlling abi-related settings
  o additinal fields in struct exec_domain for networking purposes
  o general code cleanup
  o personality.h is no more directly included in sched.h, to
    avoid namespace corruption.


Please consider applying.

	Christoph

-- 
Of course it doesn't work. We've performed a software upgrade.


